commit.message:
Address review comments

- _token_classes value type can be TokenBase
- Doc's self.result can be List[str], removing the need for 2 casts
- Relax one place to accept just Any
doc: add type hints
simpledoc: add type hints

Travis: disable Python 2.6, 3.2 & 3.3 build

Because travis-ci-language-archives no longer host these versions.

indentation: add type hints

`nosetests && mypy -2 --strict yattag/indentation.py|grep
indentation.py` passes with these. Note that the tokenizer does a lot of
duck typing, so the amount of Any type hints are a bit larger than
usual.
version 1.12.2
fixing issue with docstrings and newline characters
version 1.12.1
documenting the stag_end and nl2br options of the SimpleDoc constructor
version 1.12.0
links to yattag.org now start with https
adding nl2br option as requested in issue https://github.com/leforestier/yattag/issues/48
version 1.11.2

Faster indent function

The indent function was too slow. The issue had been raised in https://github.com/leforestier/yattag/issues/46

It is now faster
version 1.11.1
removing Python 3.7 from travis.yml (Python 3.7 not available on travis)
adding Python 3.7 classifier to setup.py
removing python 3.4 from travis.yml since it's apparently no longer available on travis
